9 SECTION 2A.3. Additional Rental Assistance. – Effective retroactively to October
10 25, 2024, Section 4B.7 of S.L. 2024-53 reads as rewritten:
11 "SECTION 4B.7. Of the funds appropriated in this act to the Department of Health and
12 Human Services, Division of Social Services (Division), the sum of one million dollars
13 ($1,000,000) in nonrecurring funds shall be allocated to county departments of social services to
14 provide rental assistance to individuals who reside, temporarily or permanently, in counties in
15 the affected area that qualify for FEMA Individual and Public Assistance Categories A-G.
16 Assistance shall be limited to households at or below two hundred percent (200%) of the federal
17 poverty level who have suffered hardship due to the impacts of Hurricane Helene. These
18 households shall receive a one-time payment up to two payments, as determined by the county
19 departments of social services, each in an amount up to the U.S. Department of Housing and
20 Urban Development's (HUD) local area Fair Market Rents (FMRs) measure for a two-bedroom
21 unit. Payments under this section shall be used to assist households facing a housing crisis, such
22 as imminent risk of eviction. County departments of social services may use up to five percent
23 (5%) of their allocated amount for administrative costs."
