1 (6) Program. – The Agricultural Disaster Crop Loss Program.
2 (7) Qualifying county. – A county in this State that meets one of the following
3 criteria:
4 a. A primary county or contiguous county listed by the USDA for an
5 agricultural disaster.
6 b. A county designated under a major disaster declaration by the
7 President of the United States under the Stafford Act (P.L. 93-288).
8 c. A county in this State deemed qualifying by State law because of
9 impacts from an agricultural disaster.
10 SECTION 2D.2.(h) Reporting. – The Department shall submit a report to the Joint
